/chicken"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/chicken.jpg?itok=jdlkaAI7" width="100" height="100" alt="Chicken" title="Chicken&#039;s many plus points - its versatility, as well as the ease and speed with which it can be cooked - make it one of the most popular meats around" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/chicken">Chicken</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">chik-en</span><p>Chicken's many plus points - its versatility, as well as the ease and speed with which itâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 garlic cloves, sliced">2 garlic cloves, sliced</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="200g pack tender stem broccoli, stems halved if very long">200g pack tender stem <a href="/glossary/broccoli" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">broccoli</a>, stems halved if very long<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-252356" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/broccoli"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/NEW-broccoli.jpg?itok=q3Vg6oAX" width="100" height="100" alt="Broccoli" title="Broccoli" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/broccoli">Broccoli</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">brok-o-lee</span><p>Like cabbage and cauliflower, broccoli is a brassica and is sometimes known by its Italian nameâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="200ml chicken stock">200ml chicken stock</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 heaped tsp cornflour">1 heaped tsp cornflour</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="1 tbsp clear honey or 2 tsp golden caster sugar">1 tbsp clear <a href="/glossary/honey" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">honey</a> or 2 tsp golden caster sugar<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-253811" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/honey"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/honey.jpg?itok=7sFDl0zl" width="100" height="100" alt="Honey" title="Honey is made by bees from the nectar they collect from flowers" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/honey">Honey</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">huh-nee</span><p>Honey is made by bees from the nectar they collect from flowers. Viscous and fragrant, it'sâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="the zest of half a lemon and the juice of a whole one">the zest of half a <a href="/glossary/lemon" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">lemon</a> and the juice of a whole one<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-259661" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/lemon"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/lemon.jpg?itok=fstxl0E6" width="100" height="100" alt="Lemon" title="Lemons are one of the most versatile fruits around, and contain a high level of Vitamin C" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/lemon">Lemon</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">le-mon</span><p>Oval in shape, with a pronouced bulge on one end, lemons are one of the most versatile fruitsâ€¦</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="a large handful of roasted cashews">a large handful of roasted <a href="/glossary/cashew" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">cashews</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-260511" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/cashew"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/cashews-resized.jpg?itok=Wh5QxNjy" width="100" height="100" alt="Cashew" title="Cashew" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/cashew">Cashew</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ka-shoo</span><p>The seeds from the 'Cashew Apple' - a tree which bears bright orange fruit and is nativeâ€¦</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Heat the oil in a large frying pan or wok. Add the chicken and fry for 3-4 minutes until golden. Remove from the pan and add the garlic and broccoli. Stir fry for a minute or so then cover and cook for 2 minutes more, until almost tender.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Mix the stock, cornflour and honey or sugar well, then pour into the pan and stir until thickened. Tip the chicken back into the pan and let it heat through, then add the lemon zest and juice, and cashew nuts. Stir, then serve straight away with basmati rice or noodles.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1044057600" class="text-style-alt">February 2003</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-102005" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe_images/recipe-image-legacy-id--1259467_8.jpg?itok=sEpxmhBf" width="324" height="294" alt="Italian-style beef stew" title="Italian-style beef stew" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/2209/italianstyle-beef-stew"> Italian-style beef stew </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-text"><div class="fivestar-static-form-item"><div class="form-item form-type-item"><div 